The discontinued bird nest from Wyson was an old variant of the Wyson seed nest obtainable before the release of the Farming Guild. After this update, the existing nests were discontinued, and newly obtained nests would instead be the current variant. All nests previously obtained would remain in banks and inventories, and the new nests obtained would provide snape grass, dragonfruit, celastrus, and redwood tree seeds. This change was made to prevent players from obtaining large quantities of the new seeds immediately upon release of the content.

Like the current version of bird nests, they were obtained from Wyson in exchange for mole claws and mole skins.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
7 July 2021
(update)

The item rotation is updated to make it more clear whether bird nests are empty or contain seeds.

10 January 2019
(update)

This variant of seed nest is discontinued and replaced with the current variant. Previously obtained nests may still exist in inventories and banks.

20 September 2018
(update)

The item's value was increased from 20 to 453 so that it would appear above logs when on the ground.

22 March 2018
(update)

The item's value was increased from 1 to 20.
